            ">Trump saves the budget one penny at a time</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/trump-saves-the-budget-one-penny-at-a-time.png" alt="Trump says he has directed the US Treasury to curb minting pennies" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"> Trump says he has directed the US Treasury to curb minting pennies. Credits: Joseph Frederick/ AP Video </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Summary: Donald Trump has ordered the US Treasury to curb minting pennies. Questions remain about Trump’s authority to unilaterally halt production.</strong></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Donald Trump announced on Truth Social that he has ordered US Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent to halt the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-02-2025-h3-8-production-of-pennies" target="_blank">production of pennies</a>, calling their minting “wasteful.” He argued that producing a one-cent coin amounts to over three cents, resulting in significant losses for taxpayers. The US Mint produced 3.2 bn pennies in 2024 for $85.3 mn, with most coins failing to re-enter circulation.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Although Trump did not mention eliminating the penny during his campaign, Elon Musk’s controversial “Department of Government Efficiency” (DOGE) highlighted its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-02-2025-h3-9-high-production-spending" target="_blank">high production spending</a> in January. Trump’s decision aligns with Musk’s broader push to cut government waste, with Musk leading initiatives to eliminate inefficiencies across federal agencies. However, critics are increasingly concerned about Musk’s expanding influence in politics.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter: blur(5px);">Many other nations, including Canada, Ireland, and the Netherlands, have already phased out their <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-02-2025-h3-10-lowest-denomination-coins" target="_blank">lowest-denomination coins</a> due to similar concerns. However, it remains unclear whether Trump can unilaterally end penny production, as <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-02-2025-h3-11-congress-oversees-us-coin-manufacturing" target="_blank">Congress oversees US coin manufacturing</a>. While Congress has previously introduced legislation to suspend or eliminate the penny, no measures have passed. The US last discontinued a low-value coin in 1857 when Congress eliminated the half-cent piece. </p>
        </mj-text>
